    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Consider re-introducing dedicated highlight groups for 'nvim-pack' confirmation report.  Needs discussing the scope of highlighting groups and the best place to define them.\n\nThe decision to remove them in favor of using `DiagnosticXxx` and `Added` / `Removed` groups is [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34009#discussion_r2178605184). I think it is relatively important to allow color schemes to adjust parts of confirmation buffer. This requires dedicated highlight groups.\n\nEarlier versions of `vim.pack` had the following set of groups added directly into 'highlight_group.c':\n\n- `PackChangeAdded` - changelog lines for added commits.\n- `PackChangeRemoved` - changelog lines for removed commits.\n- `PackHint` - plugin hints (state name after update, available tags).\n- `PackInfo` - plugin info (path, states).\n- `PackMsgBreaking` - message of the breaking commit.\n- `PackTitleError` - title for plugins that had error during update.\n- `PackTitleSame` - title for plugins that have no updates to apply.\n- `PackTitleUpdate` - title for plugins that have updates to apply.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think it might be worth revisiting this now. Not only is using stuff like `DiagnosticWarn` for headings a bit weird (they aren't warnings!), but it can look quite ugly under some colorschemes (see https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/39935).\n\nThere might be an argument for leaving `Added`/`Removed` as they are as they are being used \"correctly\" by `vim.pack`, unlike with `Diagnostic*`.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-25T01:12:05Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34768#issuecomment-4530802135",
            "id": 4530802135,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/34768",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM8AAAABDg6N1w",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
            "pin": null,
