        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think it is reasonable, but here is the [quote of the opposite point of view](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34009#discussion_r2182540320):\n\n> every feature thinks it's the most important feature and needs its own special highlights :P\n\n---\n\n> Not only is using stuff like `DiagnosticWarn` for headings a bit weird (they aren't warnings!), ...\n\nMore generally, \"warning\" is something that is meant to draw user's attention, but it is not critical (like \"error\"). I'd argue more that headings are not diagnostic.\n\n> ... but it can look quite ugly under some colorschemes (see [#39935](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/39935)).\n\nThat is the fault of the color scheme to define such highlight groups. If it is not readable in the confirmation buffer, it would be not readable where it is actually meant to be used. Explicitly setting foreground color to be opposite of the bright background is the more proper solution on the color scheme side.",
